snippet: Lockheed Martin’s F-35 Joint Strike Fighter, the nation’s most expensive arms program, could also see delays.
lead_paragraph: Lockheed Martin’s F-35 Joint Strike Fighter, the nation’s most expensive arms program, could face additional costs and delays beyond those that prompted the Pentagon to overhaul the effort earlier this year, an industry consultant said Monday.
